	(375,4,'mm-ceratosaurus','Ceratosaurus','2009-03-18',1,'','','image','<p>Point One: 4th Edition renames dinosaurs "behemoths" and gives them fantasier names like "macetail" and "bloodspike." Which okay sure whatever.\r\n\r\n<p>Point Two: I think you have to feel pretty secure in your relationship with your god if you\'re going to start saying shit like that about Gruumsh.\r\n\r\n<p>Point Three: Yes, "fantasier."'),
	(376,1,'probablylose','You Probably Lose','2009-03-17',0,'','','html','Requires Flash 9 or higher, and a certain fortitude.'),
	(377,1,'catsanddogs','Cats and Dogs','2009-03-19',1,'','','image','<p>\r\nI spent a few minutes figuring out whether "beekeepers\' convention" or "apiarists\' convention" is more common.\r\n<p>\r\nI also did this one with a fixed-width pen (in Photoshop) and it was interesting but I don\'t think I\'m going to be doing that again.'),
	(378,6,'forumville-opinions','Forumville: On Opinions','2009-03-20',1,'','','image','No comments on this, so instead I\'ll recommend another webcomic. How about <a href="http://www.sheldoncomics.com/">Sheldon</a>? I don\'t think I\'ve plugged Sheldon. It\'s got a duck and the duck has a lizard so how can that possibly be bad? It is sitting there, waiting to be enjoyed.'),
	(379,3,'lore-startrek','Lore: Star Trek','2009-03-23',1,'','','image','I do not know whether the movie will be good or not, but I am quite certain it will have a better theme song than <cite>Enterprise</cite>'),
	(380,3,'lore-speedboatracers','Lore: Speedboat Racers','2009-03-24',1,'','','image','Harvey Wallbanger: Pour one shot vodka over ice, fill with orange juice, float Galliano on top'),
	(381,1,'knob','Knob','2009-03-25',1,'','','image','Yeah, it\'s not Monster Manual Comix. It wasn\'t coming together so instead you get this odd thing.'),
	(382,4,'mm-bulette','Bulette','2009-03-26',1,'','','image','I\'ve written about Bulettes -- as well as many other monsters -- before in <a href="http://www.bookofratings.com/dndmonsters3.html">The Book of Ratings</a>. Looking back at that, I see I\'ve always been fascinated with that one rot grub-infested, mustacioed adventurer. Let the historians judge me as they will!'),
	(383,6,'forumville-enjoyment','Forumville: On Enjoyment','2009-03-27',1,'','','image','I wonder if it\'s transparent which game inspired this one.'),
	(384,3,'lore-reallygood','Lore: Really Good','2009-03-30',1,'','','image','Man, I\'ve doomed myself with this one. Some time within the next ten years, someone\'s going to make me go golfing, and I\'m going to totally love it. And people are going to say "Hey, what about that cartoon you did?" And I\'m going to say "Shut up, I need to make this putt."\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTequila Sunrise: Orange juice over ice with a shot of tequila and a dash of grenadine'),
	(385,1,'apostlenicknames','Apostolic Nicknames','2009-03-31',1,'','','image','Opinions differ as to whether the John referred to as "Pretty Pony Princess" in Mark 7:22 is the same John referred to as "Alligator Man" in 1 Timothy 1:10.'),
	(386,4,'mm-demogorgon','Demogorgon','2009-04-01',1,'','','image','"Demogorgon has two heads which bear the visages of \r\nevil baboons or perhaps mandrills" -- Monster Manual (1977)\r\n<p>\r\nI am kind of unnerved by the Monster Manual\'s indecision on this matter. If the MM doesn\'t know, how can any of us know? How can Demogorgon himself know?\r\n<p>\r\nUpdate: Looks like ol\' Demogorgon is going to be on the cover of the 4e Monster Manual 2, <a href="/images/mm2.jpg">looking much way more awesomer</a> than in 1977.\r\n<p>\r\nThose are definitely mandrill heads.'),
	(387,1,'magicitems','Magic Items of Interest','2009-04-02',1,'','','html','Wizards of the Coast had some fun <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/4news/20090402">April Fool\'s Day features</a> this year, including a usable but silly mini-adventure and an unusable but silly character class preview by Gabe and Tycho.\r\n<p>\r\nThis must have gotten to me, because the idea of the Coat of Fresh Paint came to me in my sleep last night. I decided to go with it. This will probably be gibberish to anyone who doesn\'t play D&D 4th Edition. Sorry about that, we\'ll be back to the cartoons tomorrow.\r\n<p>\r\nAt any rate, these items are probably unbalanced in some way, but if you don\'t mind that they should be usable in your campaign.'),
	(388,6,'forumville-civility','Forumville: On Civility','2009-04-03',1,'','','image','Forumville does have a head honcho. I thought he might show up in this one, but things didn\'t lean that way.\r\n<p>\r\nAlso! There\'s now a shirt available in the <a href="http://badgods.com/store.html">Bad Gods Store</a>. Proceeds go directly to buying the pixels that make up Bad Gods.'),
	(389,2,'wormwood-hotdogs1','Hot Dog With The Works, Page 1','2009-04-06',1,'','','image','Okay, time for a story arc. This should last at least three and no more than four thousand strips.'),
	(390,2,'wormwood-hotdogs2','Hot Dog With The Works, Page 2','2009-04-07',1,'','','image','I could have drawn the guy in the last panel wearing a green bowler cap and a green suit with a shamrock on the lapel and carrying a mug of beer in one hand and one of those pipes with the long curvy stem in the other hand, but I am the <em>master of understatement</em>.'),
	(391,2,'wormwood-hotdogs3','Hot Dog With The Works, Page 3','2009-04-08',1,'','','image','Kids, make sure to use a fresh, sterilized needle when injecting any meat-based snack.'),
	(392,2,'wormwood-hotdogs4','Hot Dog With The Works, Page 4','2009-04-09',1,'','','image','It\'s always startling to see the profile of a character usually shown in three-quarters perspective. I figured I\'d get it out of the way early.'),
	(393,3,'lore-acommune','Lore: A Commune','2009-04-10',1,'','','image','Grasshopper: Equal parts green creme de menthe, white creme de cacao, and cream, shaken with ice and strained into a cocktail glass. Basically an alcoholic Shamrock Shake.'),
	(394,2,'wormwood-intern1','Internal Affairs, Page 1','2009-04-13',1,'','','image','I had almost finished this comic when I remembered that Wormwood had run someone over in a truck at the beginning of the series, not a car. I wouldn\'t expect a lot of strict continuity from Sean and Wormwood, but I changed it to get that right.'),
	(395,2,'wormwood-intern2','Internal Affairs, Page 2','2009-04-14',1,'','','image','The green character there started out as a beholder-like floating thing with eyestalks, and somewhere in the design process he got turned upside down.'),
	(396,2,'wormwood-intern3','Internal Affairs, Page 3','2009-04-15',1,'','','image','I did research for this one! With the assistance of a small cadre of Twitterfolk, I determined that tentacles stay more or less the same size and shape, while pseudopods can be extended, retracted, and changed in shape and volume. I don\'t know if that\'s the actual biological definition, but as far as the comic is concerned it\'s the offical Satanic definition.'),
