	(401,2,'wormwood-seatofpower1','The Seat of Power, Page 1','2009-04-28',1,'','','image','You\'d think that it would be easy doing laundry for someone whose only items of clothing are black robes and colorful printed boxers, but then you\'d underestimate Wormwood\'s ability to attract unspeakable stains.'),
	(402,2,'wormwood-seatofpower2','The Seat of Power, Page 2','2009-04-29',1,'','','image','Ah, toilet humor! I considered changing the artifact to something less pleasing to the sensibilities of eight-year-olds, but then I thought of the title of this arc and that pretty much sealed it.'),
	(403,2,'wormwood-seatofpower3','The Seat of Power, Page 3','2009-04-30',1,'','','image','If I am questioned by the authorities, "Kindergarten Cutter" is about a four-year-old skipping class to cruise the Sunset Strip in a ragtop GTO equipped with a certified child seat.'),
	(404,4,'mm-giantant','Giant Ant','2009-05-01',1,'','','image','The 1977 Monster Manual is chock full of giant animals -- ants, eagles, even otters. But there\'s little consistency to gigantism, either in absolute or relative size. A giant ant is two feet long, while a giant badger is twice the size of a regular badger. A giant lynx appears to be about the size of a grown man, while a giant slug looks to be at least thirty feet long. What does this prove? Almost nothing!\r\n<p>\r\nAlso, that\'s one of the more bizarre speech balloons I\'ve drawn there in panel two. I hope it\'s clear that it\'s Gregoric talking, not the wall itself.'),
	(405,2,'wormwood-seatofpower4','The Seat of Power, Page 4','2009-05-04',1,'','','image','I believe this is the first time I\'ve ever drawn Wormwood with anything other than a huge grin, even in my sketchbook. '),
	(406,2,'wormwood-seatofpower5','The Seat of Power, Page 5','2009-05-05',1,'','','image','It\'s a tough thing to lose a friend because you broke into his house and smoked all his fixtures. That\'s when you know you need help.'),
	(407,2,'wormwood-seatofpower6','The Seat of Power, Page 6','2009-05-06',1,'','','image','Originally, I just wrote "juicyfruit ass-packet" as a placeholder, intending to go back and replace it with some other swear when I came up with a better one. Some folks on <a href="http://www.twitter.com/loresjoberg">Twitter</a> convinced me to leave it as-is, so there you have it.'),
	(408,2,'wormwood-seatofpower7','The Seat of Power, Page 7','2009-05-07',1,'','','image','Cue angry e-mail from Scotsmen upset at the implication that there are parts of the sheep they won\'t eat.'),
	(409,3,'lore-trackdown','Lore: Track Down','2009-05-08',1,'','','image','I\'m quoting myself from Twitter, yes. What can I say, non-Twitterfolk deserve entertainment too.\r\n<p>\r\nOld Fashioned: Muddle 1 cube sugar, 1 tsp water, 1 dash Angostura bitters in an old-fashioned or lowball glass. Add 2 oz. bourbon, twist of lemon, and two or three ice cubes. Stir. Garnish with maraschino cherry, orange slice.'),
	(411,2,'wormwood-seatofpower8','The Seat of Power, Page 8','2009-05-10',1,'','','image','I don\'t have anything to say about this strip, so I\'m going to plug the new <a href="http://www.goats.com/store/typewriters/">Goats book</a>, available for pre-order. If you\'re not familiar with Goats, it\'s a great way to get intimate with Jon\'s dimension-spanning epic. If you are familiar with Goats, it\'s a nice way to show support for a great strip and leave it lying around to get other people hooked on it.\r\n<p>\r\nIn addition, I wrote the foreword for the third book in this series, so you may as well prepare yourself now.'),
	(412,2,'wormwood-seatofpower9','The Seat of Power, Page 9','2009-05-12',1,'','','image','Because, you see, the Number of the Beast is in the Book of Revelation, so...yeah.'),
	(413,2,'wormwood-seatofpower10','The Seat of Power, Page 10','2009-05-13',1,'','','image','Rejected DDR music onomatopoeia: "tscshhh tscshhh tscshhh", "THUP THUP THUP", "vee vee VEE VEE v\'vee vee V\'VEE VEE"'),
	(414,2,'wormwood-seatofpower11','The Seat of Power, Page 11','2009-05-14',1,'','','image','Actually, Batman is the Batman of fucking.'),
	(415,4,'mm-rakshasa','Rakshasa','2009-05-15',1,'','','image','The requirements for downing a rakshasa have gone down over the years. Blessed crossbow bolts are no longer part of the equation in the latest version.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, later versions of the rakshasa have backwards hands, so that\'s nice.'),
