	(426,2,'wormwood-seatofpower18','The Seat of Power, Page 18','2009-06-02',1,'','','image','<b>Underground Kumite</b>\r\n<p>\r\nIt has not been established canonically what role, if any, <a href="http://badgods.com/wormwood-seatofpower18.html">Wormwood</a> and <a href="http://badgods.com/wormwood-seatofpower18.html">John Hodgman</a> played in the underground kumite tourney mentioned in "<a href="http://badgods.com/wormwood-seatofpower18.html">The The Seat of Power</a>, Part 18." Author speculation is that they were <a href="http://badgods.com/wormwood-seatofpower18.html">gambling</a> on the event and the <a href="http://badgods.com/wormwood-seatofpower18.html">laptop</a> won by Wormwood was part of a wager, but there remains the possibility that they were participants, managers, <a href="http://badgods.com/wormwood-seatofpower18.html">snack vendors</a>, or simply enjoy underground kumite tournaments as a pleasant background to games of <a href="http://badgods.com/wormwood-seatofpower18.html">cribbage</a>.\r\n<p>\r\n(Just working on the eventual Sean and Wormwood wiki.)'),
	(427,2,'wormwood-seatofpower19','The Seat of Power, Page 19','2009-06-03',1,'','','image','I had that <a href="http://www.wigu.com/">Topato</a> sticker, or one very like it, on my laptop. It reads "I am made of poison." That is not a phrase airport security guys like to see.'),
